    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh Independence Study for CPB Pump CFD Model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted across three successive mesh densities (coarse 2.1M cells, medium 5.8M cells, fine 14.3M cells) to establish discretization-error bounds for the hemolysis scalar transport equation. Grid convergence index (GCI) was computed per Roache (1994) for pressure rise, flow-weighted shear stress, and hemolysis index at all five operating points. The study concluded that the medium mesh yields GCI < 3% for all QoIs and was selected for production runs.",
    "activityType": "MeshRefinementStudy",
